 
<!-- PJG STAG 4703 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The applicant should include a plan to train at least 1,000 mental health care providers and students in training programs
for each of the 3 years of the grant. None of the training offerings may exceed 180 days. Applicants must include a plan
to recruit gay and bisexual men, women and minorities as trainers and trainees.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The applicant should demonstrate specialized mental health expertise, e.g., a psychiatry, psychology or social
work department in an academic institution, a mental health professional organization, or another mental health
organization.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The following are activities that a Mental Health Care Provider Education in HIV/AIDS project must include:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
Training Activities
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
&bull;The incorporation of emerging research knowledge of neuropsychiatric and psychosocial aspects of HIV/AIDS
into the curriculum.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Training for providers on aspects of the needs of individuals at risk, including gay and bisexual men, racial
and ethnic minorities, injecting drug users and their sex partners, sex workers, women, infants, children, adolescents,
and sex partners of people with HIV/AIDS.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Training for mental health professionals and personnel who serve people with serious mental illness, both
in inpatient and outpatient settings.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The recruitment of gay and bisexual men, women and individuals from minority populations as trainers and trainees.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Training for providers in prevention strategies and risk reduction to decrease the transmission of HIV infection.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Training for providers to recognize, treat, or refer individuals with the psychiatric and neuropsychiatric
complications of HIV infection and their clinical manifestation such as delirium, dementia, organic mood disorder,
depression, and adjustment disorders.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Training for providers about pre- and post-HIV antibody testing counseling.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
Integration of Mental Health and Health Training
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
&bull;Evidence of collaboration with relevant community-based AIDS organizations, medical and health professions
schools, mental health professional organizations, hospitals, substance abuse treatment providers, and other
health professions organizations, and local training programs, such as the HRSA AETC Program.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;An integrated biopsychosocial approach to understanding HIV/AIDS.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
Mental Health Expertise
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
&bull;Mental health HIV/AIDS expertise demonstrated by key staff trained in the core mental health disciplines
(psychiatry, psychology, marriage and family therapy/counseling, social work, nursing) and experienced with
HIV/AIDS.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Inclusion of at least five (5) provider groups in the training project (psychiatrists, psychologists, social
workers, medical students, primary care residents, psychiatry residents, nurses, counselors, the clergy and other
spiritual providers, etc.).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

